    "model_response": "ROOT_CAUSE: Container {{SVC}} on pod {{POD}} ({{NS}}) is being OOMKilled — its working set reached 524MB (97.7%) against a 512Mi cgroup memory limit, so the kernel OOM-killer terminated it with exit code 137. Two of three replicas ({{POD}}, {{POD2}}) are in OOM-driven crash loops, breaching the container_memory_working_set_bytes SLO (524288000 vs 200000000). The memory limit is too low for the workload's working set.\nROOT_CAUSE_CATEGORY: resource_exhaustion\nVALIDATED_CLAIMS:\n- Pod {{POD}} last_state.terminated reason=OOMKilled, exitCode=137, restart_count=4 [evidence: k8s_pods]\n- Kernel 'Memory cgroup out of memory: Killed process ... (524288000 bytes used, limit 536870912 bytes)' on {{POD}} [evidence: k8s_events]\n- Pod log 'OOMKILLED detected on payments: rss 524MB exceeded cgroup limit 512MB' then SIGKILL(137) [evidence: k8s_pod_logs]\n- container_memory_working_set_bytes=524288000 (97.7% of 512Mi limit) vs 200MB SLO, ramping 268MB->524MB over 4m [evidence: prometheus_metrics]\n- Container limits.memory=512Mi with working set exceeding it [evidence: k8s_pods]\nNON_VALIDATED_CLAIMS:\n- Not a bad deploy: image payments:1.8.3 is unchanged from previous revision 6 and the rollout reports Available/MinimumReplicasAvailable [evidence: k8s_deployments, k8s_events]\n- Not node_failure: {{NODE}} Ready=True, MemoryPressure=False, 78% memory free — the kill is container-cgroup scoped, not node scoped [evidence: k8s_node_health]\n- Not dependency_failure: the payments DB 'context deadline exceeded' timeouts are downstream of the OOM restarts dropping connections, not the cause [evidence: k8s_pod_logs, k8s_events]\nCAUSAL_CHAIN:\n- payments working set grows past the 512Mi cgroup limit -> kernel OOM-killer sends SIGKILL (exit 137) -> kubelet restarts the container (BackOff) -> 2/3 replicas crash-loop, ready 1/3 -> container_memory_working_set_bytes breaches the 200MB SLO and checkout path degrades."
  },
